# Layer boundaries

**Critical rule.** When editing related files, if you notice existing code or docs that violate this rule — even outside your current task — **flag it to the user as a high concern** before or alongside your main work. Do not silently ignore, copy the pattern, or defer without mention.

Read [DESIGN.md — Architecture](../../DESIGN.md#architecture) and [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).

## Layers

| Layer | Path | Contains | Must not contain |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **core** | `src/core/` | Models, domain mutations, validation, import/export formats, application services | React, Mantine, DOM APIs, `localStorage`, format wire string literals in domain logic |
| **integrations** | `src/integrations/` | IndexedDB/localStorage ports, Google Drive, repeater HTTP clients | React components; business rules that belong in core |
| **app** | `src/app/` | Routes, features, components, thin React state adapters | Direct calls to format adapter internals; CPS column names or wire sentinels hard-coded in UI |

## Dependency direction

```text
app → core
integrations → core
```

**Never** `core` → `app`. **Never** `core` → `integrations`.

Routes and components call **application services** (`importIntoLibrary`, `exportBuild`, `assemble`, …), not format adapters or low-level mutations ad hoc.

## Anti-patterns

- Importing React or Mantine in `src/core/`
- `src/app/` components parsing CPS CSV columns or comparing wire strings (`"Master"`, `"P2"`)
- Persistence schema or IndexedDB calls inside `src/core/`
- Format-specific cardinality checks in library CRUD UI (defer to export warnings)
